(AMD)

2. vGPU setup
Guides
-https://gist.github.com/scyto/e4e3de35ee23fdb4ae5d5a3b85c16ed3
-https://www.derekseaman.com/2024/07/proxmox-ve-8-2-windows-11-vgpu-vt-d-passthrough-with-intel-alder-lake.html
apt update && apt install pve-headers-$(uname -r)
apt install git sysfsutils dkms build-* unzip -y
nano /etc/apt/sources.list
apt update && apt install intel-media-va-driver-non-free intel-gpu-tools vainfo
wget -r -nd -e robots=no -A '*.bin' --accept-regex '/plain/' https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/firmware/linux-firmware.git/tree/i915/adlp_dmc.bin
cp adlp_dmc.bin /lib/firmware/i915/
cd ~
git clone https://github.com/strongtz/i915-sriov-dkms.git
cd i915-sriov-dkms
nano dkms.conf
cd ~
mv i915-sriov-dkms/ /usr/src/i915-sriov-dkms-6.5
dkms install --force -m i915-sriov-dkms -v 6.5
cd /etc/default/
ls
cp grub /root/grub.passthrough
nano grub
nano grub
update-grub
update-initramfs -u
echo "devices/pci0000:00/0000:00:02.0/sriov_numvfs = 2" > /etc/sysfs.conf
reboot

3. Network setup
Proxmox Management port Example
physical -> brTrunk(VLAN Aware = Yes) -> vlanxxx (Assign IP information to this, if vlanxxx is dedicated to management will be used on other Guests.
physical -> brTrunk -> vlanxxx -> LAN (Assign IP information to this, if LAN will be used on other Guests.
physical -> brTrunk -> vlanxxx -> <NAME> (No IP needed) 



